<title>SPAIN: Peseta is giving proof of stability - Montoro.</title>
<headline>Peseta is giving proof of stability - Montoro.</headline>
<dateline>MADRID 1997-02-25</dateline>
<text>
<p>The peseta is showing itself as a stable currency, as required by the prospective entrance into the European single currency, Spanish Economy Minister Cristobal Montoro said on Tuesday.</p>
<p>&quot;The peseta is moving together with the main currency (the dollar)...the peseta is showing a stable position, and it is also well-consolidated,&quot; Montoro said at a news conference.</p>
<p>He also said &quot;we (Spain) are exporting as never before.&quot;</p>
<p>Montoro added Spain is bringing ahead structural reform to rule out competitive devaluation in the future.</p>
<p>--Madrid Newsroom + 341 585 8340</p>
